SIMPLE: unstock
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unstock
<hw>Un*stock"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>stock</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of a stock; to remove the stock from; to
loose from that which fixes, or holds fast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To remove from the stocks, as a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unstockinged</ent>⟦br⟧
